    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (79.92) and **James Wood** (73.18) acting as our offensive anchors. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** benefits significantly from the matchup against Arrighetti; the combination of a high-ceiling park and an exploitable 5.10 xERA starter, paired with the added value of a slow delivery allowing for SB opportunities, vaults him into our top tier. Similarly, **James Wood** remains a priority start at the top of the order. While his matchup against Hudson is neutral, the sheer volume of plate appearances promised by the leadoff spot makes him a high-floor play in a category-starved environment. **Corbin Carroll** (71.54) rounds out our elite grouping, with his projected xwOBA of 0.372 signaling a breakout performance against King.\n\nOur most difficult roster decision involved **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who landed just shy of our starting threshold with a 39.32 efficiency score. The optimizer weighed his base projection against the difficulty of facing Detmers and a negative platoon split that effectively neutralized his power potential, dropping him just below the 40-point \"Zebras Floor.\" Conversely, we are keeping a close watch on **Dalton Rushing** (46.97) and **Luis Campusano** (43.12). While both are technically starts, their low scores reflect the headwinds created by high-skill opposing arms and poor lineup positioning. **Dalton Rushing** in particular faces a tough test against Imanaga; however, we are hoping the wind conditions in his park provide enough of a boost to mitigate the negative impact of his #7 spot in the order.\n\nRisk management remains our primary focus today. Beyond the cautious outlook for our catchers, we are monitoring the start for **Mickey Moniak** (50.49). While his platoon advantage against McLean is a massive +14%, the \"Wind In\" advisory and the unfavorable park factors have compressed his ceiling. We are effectively betting on his speed to salvage value if the ball stays in the yard. We have confirmed that **Josh Naylor** and **Giancarlo Stanton** remain out of their respective lineups, ensuring that our active roster is optimized for today's specific 5x5 needs while conserving our limited game caps for the more favorable matchups arriving later in the weekend.",
